durgapur government college, india, is the only government college not only in the home district of burdwan, but also in the neighbouring districts of bankura, purulia and birbhum. it was established on 15 september 1970 and was affiliated to the university of burdwan. now it is affiliated to kazi nazrul university. it is funded and administered by the government of west bengal. direct administrative control lies with the director of public instruction, higher education directorate, government of west bengal. the college offers 3-year undergraduate degree courses in arts, science and commerce as well as postgraduate courses in geology, conservation biology and chemistry.